thread.title: Chaminade Flies Over Nazareth

title: Chaminade Flies Over Nazareth
text: Talk about it in the nychoops Message Boards JAMAICA, NY - It's a common expression in basketball. "Live by the jay. Die by the jay." While the term usually applies to the losing team, on Thursday at the Alliance Back-to-School Classic , the Chaminade Flyers thrived by implementing an effective aerial assault that took down Brooklyn's Nazareth Kingsmen, 50-35.The Flyers were ice cold from the perimeter at the onset of the game and it appeared as if Nazareth would have the upper hand throughout the contest. Down 5-zip early, Chaminade would eventually find its rhythm as Ryan Dean '16 began to heat up, With 11:54 left in the half, a trey by the senior point guard would put the Mineola, NY squad out in front.Naz did respond with a deuce from Jahpet Chambers '16 to which Ryan countered with a trey. The Flyers also began so reap dividends from their zone defense which help limit the Kingsmen offensive options. That and crisp ball movement would continuously keep Nazareth at bay throughout the half. Kobe Telfair manage to help keep the Kingsmen in the hunt but they still trailed 20-17 as the second half commenced.The Flyers quickly doubled its lead as Quinn Suydam '16 followed suit and netted the three-pointer. That an yet another three ball from Dean launched Chaminade's lead up to 11 points with 10:20 left to play. Eventually Nazareth's deficit grew to 22 points as Owen Prendergast '16 joined in from the perimeter. With only 2 minutes left to play, the Kingsmen simply didn't have the firepower to compete.Dean and Suydam led the way for Chaminade with 12 points each. Prendergast added 10 points. Chambers paced the Kingsmen with 11 points. FEATURED PRODUCT
